      "message": "Line 85: 🟡 Suggestion: The default value `false` for `shutdownConnections` preserves backward compatibility, which is good. However, SWIG\u0027s handling of default parameters in Java can be inconsistent across versions. Verify that the generated Java binding correctly produces both a two-argument and a three-argument overload, or alternatively define an explicit overload without the default to guarantee ABI compatibility with existing callers:\n```suggestion\nvoid setAccountActive(const std::string\u0026 accountId, bool active, bool shutdownConnections);\n```\nIf you take this route, add a two-argument convenience wrapper on the Java side. Otherwise, confirm the SWIG version in use generates proper overloads for default arguments (requires `%feature(\"compactdefaultargs\")` or similar).",
